//Steps to download Tomcat server on mac machine
1. Ensure that you have a version of Java installed on the system.
	- you can check the version of java on the mac by using the below command:
		$ java -version
2. Download the latest version of Apache tomcat from their website. For mac, download the 'tar.gz' file.
3. Upon downloading, move the file to the desired folder and extract the content of the .gz file
4. Open terminal >> navigate to the folder where tomcat is extracted >> execute the 'startup.sh' file
5. Tomcat server will startup
